node.text: The month of April has been wild to say the least haha. We had our third baby boy, I moved out of my old studio and started to turn this shed into my new studio! Here’s the progress so far! #yagetme #studio #studiolife #musicstudio #producer

node.title: Turning a shed into a studio

node.text:
Creating a vocal lead with the Omnivox by @slatedigital (free in my bio until March 1) ⠀
⠀
In this beat, I felt like there was one thing missing in the top end. I decided to throw in a vocal lead, chop it up a bit and blend with a high and low octave of the sample after pitching it to the key of the beat. ⠀
⠀
#vocals #vocalsamples #flstudio #flstudiotips #vocaltips #vocalchops #vocalchop #producertips #slatedigital

I can’t believe we are less than 24 hours away from Vocal Hacking going live for the early bird listers! 

I’ve been working so hard over the last three months on this course and it is finally about to come out.

This course has everything that I’ve learned in the last 17 years about Vocal Production in a very easy to digest 5 hour online course. 

Join the early bird list if you haven’t and get ready to become a better audio engineer and increase that revenue! 

Ya Get Me

node.text:
Grab this in my bio! (Read below) 

This is for anyone that’s interested in Vocal Production and wants a free reverb / delay send mixer template with all routing and stock plugins  included! 

When you sign up for the template, you’ll also be added to the Vocal Hacking Early Bird list if you’re not in it yet… 

This is great because if you’re interested in vocal production with FL Studio, I’m opening my online course THIS SUNDAY for the early bird list only. Then Monday for the general public! 

Can’t wait to see you in the vocal hacking community! 

Ya Get Me

#recordvocals #mixingvocals #vocals #vocalproduction #recordingstudio #Flstudio #flstudio20 #producertips #808 #flstudiotips #producer #prod #musicproducer #musicproduction #makingbeats #beatmaker #producers #flgang

I am SUPER excited that registration for my online course "Vocal Hacking" will open in a few days.

So,

If you’ve signed up for the early-bird waitlist you’re lucky because your chances of getting a spot are a lot higher.

Again I’ll only be taking a small handful of new students and working with them side by side to master their vocal production. 

If you’re not signed up to the early-bird waitlist, you still have a little bit of time to sign up in my bio. 

But on a more important note: 

Here's how to make sure you get a spot….

1. Make sure you're on the early-bird waiting list 
2. Open your inbox on Sunday, 12th of September at 1PM EST
3. Refresh your inbox until you receive the early-bird registration email
4. Open the email, click on the link and secure your spot asap

If you follow these exact instructions you should have no problems getting into the class. But really make sure you sign up on Sunday, at 1PM EST.

It might be a good idea to set up a reminder on your phone so you don't miss the deadline. There's going to be a rush to the registration page on Sunday, so make sure you're one of the first to visit the signup page and lock in your spot.

I hope you can make it into the class.

Ya Get Me

node.text:
In this video I will be showing you my biggest workflow / recording secret. (Vocal Hacking Early Bird Link in Bio)

I call it my live vocal fx chain.

This is something I’ve never shown anyone online how to do. It will drastically speed up your recording workflow, resulting in happier clients, cleaner recordings, and more revenue. 

It really is a game-changer.

And what's wild to me is that I don’t see enough engineers doing this. 

Ya Get Me

node.text:
Old / New Studio session photo dump! Some REALLY old pics in here. (Quick story time 👇) 

It’s been a wild ride over the last 17 years! I can’t believe the people I’ve met and places I’ve been. If there’s one thing that I’ve always loved and came back to, it’s vocal engineering and mixing. 

It’s what changed my life and enabled me to leave my 9-5 job and pursue music full time. Engineering got me out of some really rough times in my life and career. 

I actually started engineering about the same time I started making beats, which is wild to think about. 

I’m really exited that now I can share all of this information that I’ve learned over the last 17 year in my new online course “Vocal Hacking” 

Ya Get Me
